text.tspan: Zeolite Y, a molecular sieve used to catalyse fractional
distillation in petroleum refining, was invented by Edith M.
Flanigen while working for Union Carbide. Flanigen also co-
invented a synthetic emerald and was the first female recipient
of the Perkin Medal in 1992.

text.data-name: Eileen Collins first flew the Space Shuttle as pilot in 1995 aboard STS-63. In recognition of her achievement as the first female Shuttle Pilot, she received the Harmon Trophy. She was also the pilot for STS-84 in 1997.
